Description: Fragment of rim and wall of a large Attic black-glazed pottery cup-skyphos; trace of handle root at right edge. Almost certainly from same vase as 1911,0606.43. Wholly glazed. Incised inscription in handle zone, rising above handle.
Curator's comments: Almost certainly from same piece as British Museum 1911,0606,43.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1713)
